    "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0301738.t006",
    "(3) LoRA and adapters can save computational costs significantly.",
    "By design, the PEFTs reduce the number of trainable parameters significantly (between 140 and 280 times less parameters).",
    "As a result, for sub-task 1 and 3, the utilisation of LoRA led to a significant decrease in the memory consumption-from 39GB to 24GB (38%), and from 20GB to 13GB (35%) respectively.",
    "For sub-task 2, the adapter achieved the best memory efficiency, while decreasing the peak VRAM usage from 23GB to 14GB (39%)."
